# Builder.io Fusion — Project Rules

Non-negotiable rules for every task. Full detail in `CLAUDE.md` and `docs/skills/`.

## Dev Server
- Start with `npm run dev`
- This is a static Astro site — no SSR, no middleware

## Environment Variables & API Keys
- Builder API key: always `import.meta.env.PUBLIC_BUILDER_API_KEY` — never hardcode
- Public vars (client-accessible): prefix with `PUBLIC_`
- Server-only vars (no `PUBLIC_`): only accessible in `.astro` frontmatter

## Component Types — Critical
- `.astro` files: server-rendered, zero JS by default — use for layout, static UI, data fetching
- `.tsx` files: React islands — add `client:load` or `client:idle` directive at the mount site
- **Fetch data in `.astro` frontmatter, pass as props to React islands**
- Never fetch Builder content inside a React component if `.astro` can do it statically

## Builder SDK
- Import from `@builder.io/sdk-react` only: `fetchOneEntry`, `fetchEntries`, `Content`, `isPreviewing`
- Use `Content` directly for rendering Builder content in React islands
- Guard `notFound` with `isPreviewing()` check: `if (!content && !isPreviewing()) return <div>404</div>`
- In `.astro` catch-all pages, use `getStaticPaths()` with `fetchEntries` to generate all paths

## Imports & Paths
- No barrel files — import components directly from their file
- Relative imports for project files (no `@/` alias configured)
- Example: `import { NavItems } from "./NavItems"` not `import { NavItems } from "@/components/Header/NavItems"`

## CSS & Styling
- CSS custom properties for all colors: `var(--background)`, `var(--foreground)`, etc.
- Tailwind v4 utilities for layout: `flex`, `grid`, `gap-*`, `p-*`, `max-w-*`
- Scoped `<style>` blocks in `.astro` components — no CSS Modules, no SCSS
- `:global(.class)` in Astro `<style>` to target React island elements
- Never hardcode hex colors — always use CSS custom properties

For Builder SDK patterns, component structure, and routing conventions, see the scoped rules in `.builder/rules/`.
